Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_area(25.10)                                          report_area(25.10)

Name
       report_area  -  Reports  the combined standard cell area in each of the
       hierarchy modules and the top-level design

Syntax
       report_area

       [-help]

       [-detail]

       [-hierarchical_instance <hinst_name>]

       [-include_physical]

       [-min_area <area_per_module>]

       [-min_count <instance_count>]

       [-out_file <filename>]

       [-show_leaf_cells]

       [-show_msv_cells]

       [-sort_by {name count area}]

       [-table_style {horizontal vertical}]

       [-summary | -depth <depth_of_hierarchy>]

       Reports the combined standard cell area in each of the  hierarchy  mod-
       ules and the top-level design. Also reports the cell area based on dif-
       ferent  cell types if the -detail option is specified. The command pro-
       vides breakdown based on the cell type (such as .is_* attributes).  The
       report  represents the design hierarchy, and therefore, provides better
       readability.

       Note: The units used in the report depend on the units used in the  li-
       brary.  The  area  for  each module is calculated from all the standard
       cells within each module using the LEF information.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each  report_area  parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man report_area

       -depth <depth_of_hierarchy>
              Specifies the depth of hierarchy, all levels if  not  specified;
              the top of the hierarchy (design) is 1.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -detail
              Report the area in different cell type (buffer, inverter, combi-
              national, flop, latch, clock_gate, macro, physical).

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -hierarchical_instance <hinst_name>
              Reports  the area of the leaf instances in the specified hierar-
              chical instance. You can use the -depth option  to  control  the
              analysis depth of the specified hierarchical instance.

              Data_type: (hinst), optional

       -include_physical
              Specifies  to include physical cells in the area calculation and
              report. By default, it reports only logical cells.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -min_count <instance_count>
              Specifies the min instance count per module. The generated  out-
              put  will  report  the  area  of hinsts with number of instances
              greater than the specified min_count value.

              Default: 0

              Data_type: float, optional

       -min_area <area_per_module>
              Specifies the min area per module.  The  generated  output  will
              report  the  area of hinsts with area greater than the specified
              min_area lib_units.

              Default: 0

              Data_type: int, optional

       -out_file <filename>
              Specifies the name of the output file.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -show_leaf_cells
              Specifies to include the leaf cells at the design level and each
              hinst level. These are the instances whose parent is  the  hinst
              display.

              Default: 0 (Shows the hinst children in the report)

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -show_msv_cells
              Includes  multiple  supply voltage cells in the report. This op-
              tion works with "-table_style vertical"

       -sort_by {name count area}
              Specifies the order of hinst names.

              Default: name

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -table_style {horizontal vertical}
              Specifies whether the base report should be expanded in the ver-
              tical or horizontal direction.

              Default: horizontal

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -summary
              It will print the area summary for the design. It will be equiv-
              alent as doing "-depth 0".

              Data_type: bool, optional

Examples
       The following command shows the standard cell area  in  different  base
       classes.

       report_area -detail

       The following command shows the leaf cells at the hinst level.

       report_area -show_leaf_cells

